Date:  0/11/2007
Source:  Open Space
Author:
Vol / Page:  71/14
Edition:
Quote:  Kaki evolved in isolation in New Zealand for about one million years and are different from poaka [pied stilt] which arrived from Australia in the early 1800s. Kaki and poaka have different plumage and behavioural differences.
